12.  RELATED DATA SETS

      Several data sets measuring solar irradiance at daily intervals are
      available.  These vary from ground-based telescope observations to
      solar-viewing satellite instruments.  The Nimbus-7 Earth Radiation
      Budget Solar Irradiance data set covers the time period from November
      16, 1978 to October 31, 1990.  The Solar Maximum Mission (SMM) Active
      Cavity Radiometer Irradiance Monitor (ACRIM) data set also collects
      daily values of solar flux.  The data set extends from February 16,
      1980 to December 31, 1988.  Detailed information on these data sets
      can be found in the NCDS data set descriptions for N-7-ERB and
      SMM_ACRIM respectively.


